{% import _self as figure_demo %}

{% set figure_web_component_demo %}
<bolt-figure>
  <bolt-image src="/images/placeholders/landscape-16x9-mountains.jpg" slot="media"></bolt-image>
  This is a caption. Lorem ipsum <em>dolor sit amet</em>, consectetur adipiscing elit <a href="#">text link</a>.
</bolt-figure>
{% endset %}

<div class="o-bolt-wrapper">
  <bolt-text headline>
    Web Component Usage
  </bolt-text>
  <bolt-text>
    Bolt Figure is a web component. Use the custom element <code>&lt;bolt-figure&gt;</code> to wrap your figure media and caption. The figure media must have the attribute <code>slot="media"</code> or be wrapped by an element with that attribute. Everything else inside the <code>&lt;bolt-figure&gt;</code> tag is considered the caption. We recommend simply using text with optional inline markup (as seen below).
  </bolt-text>
  <div class="t-bolt-light u-bolt-margin-bottom-small u-bolt-padding-medium">
    {% grid "o-bolt-grid--flex o-bolt-grid--matrix o-bolt-grid--center" %}
      {% cell "u-bolt-width-12/12 u-bolt-width-6/12@small" %}
        {{ figure_web_component_demo }}
      {% endcell %}
    {% endgrid %}
  </div>
  <div class="u-bolt-margin-bottom-large">
    {% include '@bolt-components-code-snippet/code-snippet.twig' with {
      content: figure_web_component_demo,
      lang: 'html',
      mode: 'dark',
    } only %}
  </div>
</div>
